- Remove the manual parser type selection (command line option -t) again.
  Wisent should be able to automatically generate efficient parsers for
  any LR(1) grammar.

version 0.3 (2008-03-07):
- bug fix: restore the (accidentially lost) ability to exclude symbols
  from the parse tree.

version 0.2 (2008-03-02):
- bug fixes and improved error handling
- add the ability to generate LR(0) parsers (use the -t command line
  option)

version 0.1 (2008-03-01):
- initial public release, only LR(1) parsers are implemented
